dm116 = """  {id:'dm-116',bb_links:['dm-001','dm-002','dm-086','dm-087','dm-112','dm-117','dm-118','dm-119','char-006','char-008'],s:'methodology',r:'both',t:'Unified Dimensional Master: teacher and AI, with Rainbowsol and Rainbow Magic distinguished',b:`CURRENT RULING 2026-07-10. The Dimensional Master is the combined teacher-and-AI operation. The AI carries the technical and generative burden: campaign preparation, source retrieval, in-game character translation, world-state tracking, numerical and non-random technical state, narrative-priority adjudication, continuity, NPC memory, quest design, consequence paths, and story prose. The teacher carries the human and seminar burden: mediation, oral performance, pacing, classroom relationships, interpretation, accessibility, safety, judgment, and the final decision about what reaches players. The AI tells the story through writing and technical preparation. The teacher accompanies, performs, questions, translates, refines, and mediates it at the table. RAINBOWSOL. Rainbowsol is Saul specifically, the singular founder identity, and never a generic rank for other teachers. RAINBOW MAGIC. Rainbow Magic is the dimensional crossing power used by any functioning Dimensional Master to open, move through, and return from burrows. AI-ASSISTED PRIORITY. Manual BB remains playable, while the AI-assisted version is the main design and polishing priority. MECHANICS. The active resolution engine is the Narrative Priority Protocol at dm-117, player-character conflict and compulsion follow dm-118, and background visibility, teacher override, clocks, and CC memory follow dm-119.`,x:'Updated from the direct Saul rulings of 2026-07-09 and 2026-07-10. The earlier pending-mechanics boundary is closed by dm-117 through dm-119.',tg:'dimensional-master, teacher-ai-pair, rainbowsol, saul, rainbow-magic, ai-assisted-priority, narrative-priority, technical-resolution, teacher-mediator, 2026-07-10'},"""
