new_foundations = """**F1. No dice.** Polymythdnd uses no dice, probability tables, hit chances, random reaction rolls, or hidden random resolver. Technical numbers may record state, intensity, time, distance, injury, resources, relationships, or progression, while chance itself never decides an outcome. The active resolution engine is the Narrative Priority Protocol at bb* dm-117.\n\n**F2. Unified Dimensional Master.** The Dimensional Master is the teacher-and-AI pair. The AI handles preparation, translation, state, comparison, continuity, technical resolution, and prose. The teacher handles the human room, mediation, performance, accessibility, judgment, and the final decision about what reaches players. The teacher may refine or override any AI proposal. Rainbowsol names Saul specifically, while Rainbow Magic belongs to every functioning DM pair.\n\n**F3. Narrative priority as resolution.** Resolution selects the most causally specific, exegetically faithful, internally and externally logical, well-written result that follows from the live campaign state, the character, the player’s intention and approach, academic work, relationships, preparation, environment, time, emotional modifiers, and every other relevant factor. Candidate mechanics coexist as contextual tools. No public success category is required when the narration can state exactly what happened.\n\n**F4. Reading, research, discussion, and academic work as context-sensitive substrates.** Academic engagement expands knowledge, access, leverage, abilities, relationships, quest effects, and the quality of action whenever the situation depends on that learning. It does not erase ordinary character agency in actions whose causal basis lies elsewhere. A character may still walk, speak, flee, observe, help, struggle, or make mistakes, while deeper engagement creates stronger and more precise possibilities inside a text-anchored world.\n\n**F5. Any action possible.** No predetermined action list bounds what bookworms can attempt, including cooperation, separation, disagreement, persuasion, intimidation, compulsion, theft, and harm among player characters when the world permits them. Permission to attempt never guarantees success. The Narrative Priority Protocol and the teacher’s mediation determine what follows.\n\n**F6. AI background, teacher mediation, layered visibility.** The AI carries the hidden technical and generative burden and gives the teacher a complete game-relevant rationale. Players receive the stakes and reasons their characters could reasonably understand, followed by a clear narrative result. CC* retains the consequential record.\n\n**F7. Bookworm becomes author.** The long-arc goal is that bookworms transition from bookworm-as-character-in-game to bookworm-as-co-author-of-their-own dimension. Mature bookworms author dimensions for newer bookworms. The framework operates as a living scanner without dependency on any single facilitator.\n"""
rules = rules[:old_foundations.start()] + new_foundations + rules[old_foundations.end():]

rules = rules.replace("**A4. Named title-levels.** Character-progression uses named titles instead of numerical levels. Title-progression is text-grounded — titles emerge from the reading-substrate of dimensions. The bookworm becomes \"Apprentice\" then \"Initiate\" then \"Adept\" through demonstrated reading-comprehension and in-game-action, not through XP-tracking. (Source: T114t named-title-levels.)", "**A4. Multidimensional progression with named titles.** Named titles may summarize long-arc development, while the character can progress across knowledge, academic abilities, practical skills, badges, relationships, reputation, equipment, scars, emotional patterns, symbolic development, powers, responsibilities, and narrative permissions. Individual and group progression may proceed at different rates according to actual contributions and campaign events. A new character still begins from the Level 1 or humble-baseline equivalent.")
rules = rules.replace("**A5. As-many-variables-as-possible substrate.** The AI tracks AS MANY VARIABLES AS POSSIBLE in the in-game state. Inventory, relationships, knowledge-gained, debts-owed, locations-visited, words-spoken, choices-made — all tracked. The mass-of-variables IS the substrate the AI adjudicates against. This is what allows novel-actions to be adjudicated coherently (F5). (Source: T114t many-variables-ai-substrate.)", "**A5. As-many-relevant-variables-as-possible substrate.** The AI preserves every game-relevant variable that can materially affect continuity or adjudication, including inventory, relationships, knowledge, debts, locations, words, actions, emotional states, clocks, injuries, promises, and consequences. Relevance governs use: a tracked factor influences a ruling only when it causally belongs to that situation. The system tracks fictional and educational state rather than collecting unnecessary private information about the student.")
rules = rules.replace("**Badges visible, variables invisible (T114v).** Badges are surfaced on the bookwormcard for public-witness. The underlying variables that determined badge-award remain invisible (per A5 — the AI tracks variables, doesn’t expose them). This protects the bookworm from gaming-the-variable while honoring the demonstrated skill.", "**Badges visible, adjudication layered.** Badges are surfaced on the wormcard. The teacher may inspect the complete evidence and game-relevant rationale behind an award, while players receive the relevant criteria and reasons without unnecessary backend calculations. CC* preserves the consequential record.")

old_run = re.search(r"\*\*During session\.\*\*[\s\S]*?\*\*Rainbow-note protocol", rules)
